Bougues Telecom launches 15 bln ffrs bond - paper . Bouygues Telecom is launching a 15 billion franc 10 - year bond to finance the development of its telecom infrastructure , newspaper l ' Agefi said . The bond is lead - managed by J . P Morgan and underwriters are ABN Amro Bank , BNP and Westdeutsche Landesbank Girozentrale , the paper said . Nobody was immediately available at Bouygues for comment . Bouygues said on March 30 it was in talks for a syndicated bank loan for 15 billion francs for its project to become France ' s third telecom operator after France Telecom and Cegetel of Generale des Eaux . 
